                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I doubt anyone here will be able to assuredly tell you what is doing that, but i'll try to name a few things that cross my mind.<br /><br />First, I really doubt Sony is spying on you <img src="images/cyclops_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br />as they would get into a load of trouble.<br />Is that really true that they tried that before? It almost seems too unbelievable that they would do such a thing.<br />It is possible you have your Anti-virus software configured to regularly scan files in the background for viruses and it could be scanning them on your cd-rom as well. Maybe even your spyware detection software is doing it also, I don't know as I have never used it.<br />I'm surprised you can run all of that and still get everquest to work decently, you must have a pretty good machine.<br /><br />There are a lot of programs that could be making your harddrive spin up while you're playing. CD-rom is a different story.<br />Does this happen at a specific time every day? You might want to check and see.<br />I know windowsupdate causes some crazy harddrive activity once per day for me when it checks for updates.<br /><br />The first thing you should do is turn off all visible programs on your taskbar, and try it. Next, ctrl+alt+del all unneccesary programs if it still occurs.<br />That's the easiest way to find out which program is causing the problems.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
